args:
After Pinon arrived in Muskov on a mission,
she was attacked by a strange monster.
She ended up agreeing to help the townspeople
by subduing the beasts...
Well, I've now visited every place these\nmonsters were supposedly spotted.
From what I've gathered, there are a great\nmany of them, and they appear at random\nintervals from multiple directions.
That's more or less the same thing the\nbishop told me, though I'm still not\ncertain of his end game in all of this.
You seem to be working hard, traveler.\nHow goes your progress?
Little yet to report, I fear. It is a shame,\nfor I would like to free the townspeople\nfrom this threat as quickly as possible.
You certainly are keen to help a\nbunch of strangers, aren't you?
I seek to aid all people in trouble,\nas my seniors would do.
But my hopes mean little without firm\naction to back them up. If only I had\nsomething better to go on...
Have you heard anything, sir? Any rumor,\nno matter how seemingly meaningless,\nmight prove a vital clue.
Well, I have heard one thing...
Some folks say the monsters all go to\na certain place after they attack us.
Why did no one mention this\nto me before now?
Fear stills their tongues—fear that an\noutsider might upset the paradise\nBishop Roalta has built here.
Still, it's not right for hesitation to cause\na kind soul like yourself such trouble.
If you can keep my involvement secret,\nI'll show you where they gather. Come.
*pant* *pant* I'd expected this gathering\nplace to be further outside of town.
It's definitely here. I saw them entering\ntheir lair myself. I watched from a cave,\nright over yonder...
One really showed up!\nGet behind me!
And my second as well! This one's\nstronger than the other one I fought...
But it's my first real clue—I must\ncapture it!
It deflected my attacks back at us!\nEeek!
(Trying to capture this foe is folly;\nI must prioritize driving it off!)
O Gabriel, lend me your strength!\nSigil, unleash!
I shall see Her will done!
*pant* *pant* We should be safe for now.\nAre you well, sir? Were you hurt?
You're wounded! Hold as still as you can;\nI will see you back to town.
*sigh* Well, I've done it this time.
Not only did I lose my chance to bring\ndown the monster, I got someone hurt.\nWhat am I even doing here...?
I'm certain any of my seniors would have\nhandled the whole situation magnificently.\nPerhaps this is just too much for me...
N-Nevin! But...how can this be?!\nAre you a hallucination?!
My apologies. Still, why are you here?\nWere you not investigating an incident\nin another town?
Yeah, that didn't exactly go so hot,\nso I figured I'd pop by and see you\nto switch things up a little bit.
So even you run into difficulties\nfrom time to time...
Spoiler alert: EVERYONE does.\nBut hey, let's talk shop for a hot sec:\nYou've heard about the monsters, yeah?
Yes, and they're causing me no end of\ntrouble! I took on a request to get rid\nof them, but I'm not making progress.

The ones I encountered are not unlike the
fiends of the south... But I am
at a loss as to why these things are
appearing here in the north.
So you've already run into them, eh?\nOh, and did you hear anything about the\nmonsters being ＂summoned by the dead＂?
Nothing like that, no. But there HAVE been\nother points of interest I've uncovered\nduring my investigation.
All the residents I spoke to in the course\nof my investigation have been in the\nprime of their years.
I didn't speak to a single elderly person\nor child—and in fact, I suspect there may\nnot be any in the entire town.

The majority of the citizens migrated here
because of an arrangement with the
bishop, but that shouldn't account for
such an unbalance in age.

That, combined with the monsters,
makes me believe we are dealing with
more here than the simple dissident I
was tasked with rooting out.
Yeah, that's a weird one, all right.\nStill, it doesn't seem to have anything\nto do with my case, so I guess...
Wait, hang on. No old people or kids,\nmonsters, a missing weapon, and\n＂the dead＂...
Pinon, I need you to wait here for a bit\nand...wait. Just stand there. Cool?
I've got something I need to look into\nover in the neighboring town.
If it goes well, I think we can wrap our\nmissions up at the same time—so just\ntrust Papa Bear on this one, okay?
At least tell me what is going ON! ...Bah!
I think he owes me an explanation if this\nhas something to do with MY mission!
But he did not offer one—nor did he offer\nto bring me with him. It seems I'm more\nof a burden than I thought...
*sigh* I suppose I'll just sit here like\na good little bunny and... Hmm?
...So you failed to take care of her.
F-forgive me, Bishop Roalta.\nI will accept any punishment.
Your punishment comes later. If even the\none in the nest has failed, we'll need to\ntake different measures. Come.
It's the bishop and the man I was speaking\nwith earlier. What could they be up to\nat this late hour?
I'm sorry, Nevin, but I am an apostle—\nand I will not simply loiter about and\nwait for you to save the day!
This time, I will live up to the expectations\nplaced on me and see my mission through!
